-- Clipper Windpower First-Half Revenue Drops 57% on Fewer Wind-Turbine Sales
-- B y   D o u g l a s   L y t l e
-- 2010-09-30T06:05:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-30/clipper-windpower-first-half-revenue-drops-57-on-fewer-wind-turbine-sales.html
Clipper Windpower Plc said revenue
fell to $154 million in the first half of the year from $357
million in the year ago period as the company sold fewer wind
turbines.  The company expects the second half of the year to show
further improvement as “signs of optimism and improvement
are emerging,” it said in a Regulatory News Statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Douglas Lytle at 
 dlytle@bloomberg.net  